  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed at the package level; however one validation result covering low-flow operating conditions characterises inherent variability qualitatively only, leaving the structured UQ link absent for that result. Full 13-factor assessment covers all required credibility dimensions. Decision: Accepted.",
