      "name": "Low-flow hemolysis validation — 2 LPM at 3000 RPM",
      "description": "CFD hemolysis index compared against bench measurements at the low-flow operating condition. Inherent variability in red blood cell fragility across donor samples was assessed qualitatively by the experimental team and noted in the test report; no structured probabilistic characterisation of this aleatory source was linked to this result. Predicted MIH falls within the reported experimental range, and the engineering team judged the qualitative assessment sufficient given the relatively low hemolysis magnitudes at this operating point."
