      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed; GCI for hemolysis index ranges 4–11% across operating points. High-shear impeller tip region shows GCI above threshold at two conditions, limiting achieved level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions must be fully characterised and traceable to calibrated instrumentation with uncertainty budgets.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rates measured with Coriolis flowmeter (±0.5%); rotational speed via optical encoder (±1 RPM). Fluid temperature monitored but not controlled to ±0.5 °C as required; donor blood viscosity variability documented qualitatively only."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative validation metric (e.g. E% with uncertainty) reported for each operating point; systematic bias assessed.",
      "rationale": "Percent error and NRMSE computed for all five conditions. Prediction intervals from Monte Carlo overlap experimental uncertainty bands at three of five points. Systematic over-prediction at high-shear conditions suggests model form bias not fully characterised."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (modified index of hemolysis) must be directly traceable to clinical hemolysis threshold used in device labelling.",
      "rationale": "MIH directly maps to plasma free haemoglobin threshold cited in the clinical protocol. Conversion from CFD scalar to MIH validated against published correlation; however the correlation's own uncertainty at low haemolysis levels is not propagated into the QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, blood analogue properties, and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic pump geometry used in both validation and COU. Porcine blood used in bench testing; human blood rheology applied in COU simulations — species difference introduces an unquantified extrapolation not fully bridged by the current evidence package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence criteria and floating-point round-off assessed; residuals below 1e-5 for all transport equations.",
      "rationale": "Residuals reach 1e-4 for hemolysis scalar transport at two operating points; convergence to 1e-5 not achieved within practical iteration budget. Solver error contribution estimated by Richardson extrapolation in iteration space but not formally bounded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation workflow must be documented with sufficient detail for independent reproduction; peer review of setup files completed.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup documented in internal report; peer review performed by one internal analyst. Independent external reproduction not attempted. UDF parameter selection (hemolysis model exponents) not subjected to formal sensitivity review."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive law must be justified against published validation evidence for rotating blood-contacting devices.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega selected based on literature review for rotating machinery; hemolysis power-law (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) chosen for computational tractability. Published evidence shows significant model-form error for high-shear transient exposures; no alternative model comparison performed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must have documented sources with uncertainty characterisation; sensitivity analysis identifies dominant inputs.",
      "rationale": "Fluid density and viscosity sourced from literature with ±5% bounds. Hemolysis model coefficients (C, alpha, beta) taken from single published source without uncertainty bounds. Sensitivity analysis shows hemolysis index is most sensitive to beta exponent, yet its uncertainty is uncharacterised."
    },
